# RUNNIT BACK — CORE SYSTEM

## PURPOSE
Build a high-performance sports clip network optimized for:
- attention
- retention
- monetization

---

## CORE RULES

1. CONTENT FIRST
- Quality over quantity
- No weak clips

2. MANUAL APPROVAL REQUIRED
- Nothing gets posted automatically

3. ONE OPERATOR = ONE CHANNEL
- No overlap
- Clear ownership

4. FORMAT LOCK
- 9:16 only
- No 16:9 inside vertical

5. SPEED WITH CONTROL
- Fast pipeline
- Strict validation

---

## PIPELINE

1. SOURCE → find clip
2. SELECT → choose best segment
3. HOOK → create hook
4. CAPTION → format caption
5. BOARD → multi-angle evaluation
6. APPROVAL → human decision
7. TRIM → cut clip
8. FORMAT → 9:16 conversion
9. EXPORT → generate file
10. SCHEDULE → send to Buffer
11. ANALYZE → performance feedback

---

## HARD REJECTION RULES

Reject immediately if:

- weak or unclear hook
- slow or boring segment
- no emotional trigger
- overused content
- bad format (aspect ratio)

---

## SUCCESS SIGNALS

- strong first 2 seconds
- clear tension or payoff
- recognizable moment
- loopable ending

---

## DATA STRUCTURE

Every clip must include:

post_id:
channel:
sport:
source_url:

hook:
caption:
hashtags:

timestamp_range:
duration:
aspect_ratio:

status:
owner:
created_at:

---

## ENFORCEMENT RULES

- Hooks must be under 8 words when possible
- Captions must not exceed 2 short lines
- Hashtags must be 4–6 only
- Board must include at least one negative or risk note
- Weak clips must be rejected, not improved

---

## CLIP EXECUTION RULES

- Every approved clip must include a precise timestamp range
- Default clip length: 6–15 seconds
- Clip must start immediately at action (no dead air)
- Clip must end on payoff or loop point
- If full arc is stronger than short cut, allow extended segment

---

## EXPORT REQUIREMENTS

Every APPROVED clip must include:

- post_id
- timestamp_range
- duration
- aspect_ratio = 9:16
- file name format: post_id_platform_version.mp4

---

## SYSTEM LIMITATION (CURRENT)

- System identifies and prepares clips
- System does NOT yet automatically trim video
- System does NOT yet push to Buffer automatically
- Requires backend integration (ffmpeg + Buffer API)

---

## SYSTEM RULE

If a mistake happens twice:
→ add a new rule here
→ keep it short and enforceable
